verses.text_plain: Furthermore Elihu answered and said,
verses.verse_html: 1Furthermore Elihu answered and said,

verses.text_plain: Hear my words, O ye wise men; and give ear unto me, ye that have knowledge.
verses.verse_html: 2Hear my words, O ye wise men; and give ear unto me, ye that have knowledge.

tokens.text: unto me, ye that have knowledge

verses.text_plain: For the ear trieth words, as the mouth tasteth meat.
verses.verse_html:
3For the ear trieth words, as the mouth tasteth meat. ▼
▼ mouth: Heb. palate

verses.text_plain: Let us choose to us judgment: let us know among ourselves what is good.
verses.verse_html: 4Let us choose to us judgment: let us know among ourselves what is good.

verses.text_plain: For Job hath said, I am righteous: and God hath taken away my judgment.
verses.verse_html: 5For Job hath said, I am righteous: and God hath taken away my judgment.

verses.text_plain: Should I lie against my right? my wound is incurable without transgression.
verses.verse_html:
6Should I lie against my right? my wound is incurable without transgression. ▼
▼ my wound: Heb. mine arrow

footnotes.body_html: ▼ my wound: Heb. mine arrow

verses.text_plain: What man is like Job, who drinketh up scorning like water?
verses.verse_html: 7What man is like Job, who drinketh up scorning like water?

verses.text_plain: Which goeth in company with the workers of iniquity, and walketh with wicked men.
verses.verse_html: 8Which goeth in company with the workers of iniquity, and walketh with wicked men.

verses.text_plain: For he hath said, It profiteth a man nothing that he should delight himself with God.
verses.verse_html: 9For he hath said, It profiteth a man nothing that he should delight himself with God.

verses.text_plain: Therefore hearken unto me, ye men of understanding: far be it from God, that he should do wickedness; and from the Almighty, that he should commit iniquity.
verses.verse_html:
10Therefore hearken unto me, ye men of understanding: far be it from God, that he should do wickedness; and from the Almighty, that he should commit iniquity. ▼
▼ men…: Heb. men of heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ men…: Heb. men of heart

verses.text_plain: For the work of a man shall he render unto him, and cause every man to find according to his ways.
verses.verse_html: 11For the work of a man shall he render unto him, and cause every man to find according to his ways.

tokens.text: unto him, and cause every man

verses.text_plain: Yea, surely God will not do wickedly, neither will the Almighty pervert judgment.
verses.verse_html: 12Yea, surely God will not do wickedly, neither will the Almighty pervert judgment.

verses.text_plain: Who hath given him a charge over the earth? or who hath disposed the whole world?
verses.verse_html:
13Who hath given him a charge over the earth? or who hath disposed the whole world? ▼
▼ the whole: Heb. all of it?

tokens.text: Who hath given him a charge

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the whole: Heb. all of it?
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the whole: Heb. all of it?

verses.text_plain: If he set his heart upon man, if he gather unto himself his spirit and his breath;
verses.verse_html:
14If he set his heart upon man, if he gather unto himself his spirit and his breath; ▼
▼ man: Heb. him

verses.text_plain: All flesh shall perish together, and man shall turn again unto dust.
verses.verse_html: 15All flesh shall perish together, and man shall turn again unto dust.

verses.text_plain: If now thou hast understanding, hear this: hearken to the voice of my words.
verses.verse_html: 16If now thou hast understanding, hear this: hearken to the voice of my words.

verses.text_plain: Shall even he that hateth right govern? and wilt thou condemn him that is most just?
verses.verse_html:
17Shall even he that hateth right govern? and wilt thou condemn him that is most just? ▼
▼ govern: Heb. bind?

verses.text_plain: Is it fit to say to a king, Thou art wicked? and to princes, Ye are ungodly?
verses.verse_html: 18Is it fit to say to a king, Thou art wicked? and to princes, Ye are ungodly?

verses.text_plain: How much less to him that accepteth not the persons of princes, nor regardeth the rich more than the poor? for they all are the work of his hands.
verses.verse_html: 19How much less to him that accepteth not the persons of princes, nor regardeth the rich more than the poor? for they all are the work of his hands.

verses.text_plain: In a moment shall they die, and the people shall be troubled at midnight, and pass away: and the mighty shall be taken away without hand.
verses.verse_html:
20In a moment shall they die, and the people shall be troubled at midnight, and pass away: and the mighty shall be taken away without hand. ▼
▼ the mighty…: Heb. they shall take away the mighty

footnotes.body_text: ▼ the mighty…: Heb. they shall take away the mighty
footnotes.body_html: ▼ the mighty…: Heb. they shall take away the mighty

verses.text_plain: For his eyes are upon the ways of man, and he seeth all his goings.
verses.verse_html: 21For his eyes are upon the ways of man, and he seeth all his goings.

verses.text_plain: There is no darkness, nor shadow of death, where the workers of iniquity may hide themselves.
verses.verse_html: 22There is no darkness, nor shadow of death, where the workers of iniquity may hide themselves.

verses.text_plain: For he will not lay upon man more than right; that he should enter into judgment with God.
verses.verse_html:
23For he will not lay upon man more than right; that he should enter into judgment with God. ▼
▼ enter: Heb. go

verses.text_plain: He shall break in pieces mighty men without number, and set others in their stead.
verses.verse_html:
24He shall break in pieces mighty men without number, and set others in their stead. ▼
▼ number: Heb. searching out

footnotes.body_html: ▼ number: Heb. searching out

verses.text_plain: Therefore he knoweth their works, and he overturneth them in the night, so that they are destroyed.
verses.verse_html:
25Therefore he knoweth their works, and he overturneth them in the night, so that they are destroyed. ▼
▼ destroyed: Heb. crushed

verses.text_plain: He striketh them as wicked men in the open sight of others;
verses.verse_html:
26He striketh them as wicked men in the open sight of others; ▼
▼ open…: Heb. place of beholders

footnotes.body_html: ▼ open…: Heb. place of beholders

verses.text_plain: Because they turned back from him, and would not consider any of his ways:
verses.verse_html:
27Because they turned back from him, and would not consider any of his ways: ▼
▼ him: Heb. after him

footnotes.body_html: ▼ him: Heb. after him

verses.text_plain: So that they cause the cry of the poor to come unto him, and he heareth the cry of the afflicted.
verses.verse_html: 28So that they cause the cry of the poor to come unto him, and he heareth the cry of the afflicted.

tokens.text: So that they cause the cry

verses.text_plain: When he giveth quietness, who then can make trouble? and when he hideth his face, who then can behold him? whether it be done against a nation, or against a man only:
verses.verse_html: 29When he giveth quietness, who then can make trouble? and when he hideth his face, who then can behold him? whether it be done against a nation, or against a man only:

verses.text_plain: That the hypocrite reign not, lest the people be ensnared.
verses.verse_html: 30That the hypocrite reign not, lest the people be ensnared.

verses.text_plain: Surely it is meet to be said unto God, I have borne chastisement, I will not offend any more:
verses.verse_html: 31Surely it is meet to be said unto God, I have borne chastisement, I will not offend any more:

tokens.text: Surely it is meet to be said

verses.text_plain: That which I see not teach thou me: if I have done iniquity, I will do no more.
verses.verse_html: 32That which I see not teach thou me: if I have done iniquity, I will do no more.

tokens.text: thou me: if I have done

verses.text_plain: Should it be according to thy mind? he will recompense it, whether thou refuse, or whether thou choose; and not I: therefore speak what thou knowest.
verses.verse_html:
33Should it be according to thy mind? he will recompense it, whether thou refuse, or whether thou choose; and not I: therefore speak what thou knowest. ▼
▼ according…: Heb. from with thee?

tokens.text: according to thy mind? he will recompense

footnotes.body_html: ▼ according…: Heb. from with thee?

verses.text_plain: Let men of understanding tell me, and let a wise man hearken unto me.
verses.verse_html:
34Let men of understanding tell me, and let a wise man hearken unto me. ▼
▼ of…: Heb. of heart

footnotes.body_html: ▼ of…: Heb. of heart

verses.text_plain: Job hath spoken without knowledge, and his words were without wisdom.
verses.verse_html: 35Job hath spoken without knowledge, and his words were without wisdom.

verses.text_plain: My desire is that Job may be tried unto the end because of his answers for wicked men.
verses.verse_html:
36My desire is that Job may be tried unto the end because of his answers for wicked men. ▼
▼ My…: or, My father, let Job be tried

footnotes.body_text: ▼ My…: or, My father, let Job be tried
footnotes.body_html: ▼ My…: or, My father, let Job be tried

verses.text_plain: For he addeth rebellion unto his sin, he clappeth his hands among us, and multiplieth his words against God.
verses.verse_html: 37For he addeth rebellion unto his sin, he clappeth his hands among us, and multiplieth his words against God.
